7, \"to\": 1557}, {\"ngram\": \"the men\", \"from\": 1561, \"to\": 1568}, {\"ngram\": \"theirParis 2024campaign\", \"from\": 1586, \"to\": 1609}, {\"ngram\": \"the Stade Yves-du-Manoir\", \"from\": 1627, \"to\": 1651}, {\"ngram\": \"the venue\", \"from\": 1666, \"to\": 1675}, {\"ngram\": \"Fire\", \"from\": 1769, \"to\": 1773}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They are ranked second in the world, behind the Netherlands, who they narrowly lost to in the final of last year's European Championships.\", \"from\": 1776, \"to\": 1914, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1824, \"end\": 1835, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999995191798253, \"rank\": 4.783118965925472e-07, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1891, \"end\": 1913, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA_European_Championship\", \"score\": 0.9999999283800233, \"rank\": 7.161981533540249e-08, \"text\": \"European Championships\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA_European_Championship\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA_European_Championship\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1802, \"to\": 1811}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 16-strong men's squad features a mix of youth and experience, with seven men set to make their Olympic debuts in the French capital.\", \"from\": 1916, \"to\": 2052, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2037, \"end\": 2043, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9208064234218407, \"rank\": 0.060432199998692634, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The 16-strong men's squad\", \"from\": 1916, \"to\": 1941}, {\"ngram\": \"a mix\", \"from\": 1951, \"to\": 1956}, {\"ngram\": \"youth\", \"from\": 1960, \"to\": 1965}, {\"ngram\": \"experience\", \"from\": 1970, \"to\": 1980}, {\"ngram\": \"seven men\", \"from\": 1987, \"to\": 1996}, {\"ngram\": \"their Olympic debuts\", \"from\": 2009, \"to\": 2029}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Skipper David Ames is one of two three-time Olympians to earn selection and is seeking to follow the lead of Stephen Martin and Jimmy Kirkwood, members of the Seoul team and the last Northern Irish athletes to win Olympic gold in any sport.\", \"from\": 2053, \"to\": 2293, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2061, \"end\": 2071, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Ames_(actor)\", \"score\": 0.9683031453657999, \"rank\": 0.03272727272726326, \"text\": \"David Ames\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Ames_(actor)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Ames_(actor)\"}, {\"begin\": 2170, \"end\": 2176, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\", \"score\": 0.9999981453937752, \"rank\": 1.8176548380306044e-06, \"text\": \"Martin\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\"}, {\"begin\": 2181, \"end\": 2195, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Kirkwood_(field_hockey)\", \"score\": 0.999996754062788, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jimmy Kirkwood\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Kirkwood_(field_hockey)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Kirkwood_(field_hockey)\"}, {\"begin\": 2212, \"end\": 2217, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9995738431674299, \"rank\": 0.00035643086996775547, \"text\": \"Seoul\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"two three-time Olympians\", \"from\": 2082, \"to\": 2106}, {\"ngram\": \"selection\", \"from\": 2115, \"to\": 2124}, {\"ngram\": \"the lead\", \"from\": 2150, \"to\": 2158}, {\"ngram\": \"members\", \"from\": 2197, \"to\": 2204}, {\"ngram\": \"the last Northern Irish athletes\", \"from\": 2227, \"to\": 2259}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic gold\", \"from\": 2267, \"to\": 2279}, {\"ngram\": \"any sport\", \"from\": 2283, \"to\": 2292}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Spend a few minutes in the company of the softly-spoken midfielder, and you'd never guess who his sporting inspiration was.\", \"from\": 2295, \"to\": 2418, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a few minutes\", \"from\": 2301, \"to\": 2314}, {\"ngram\": \"the company\", \"from\": 2318, \"to\": 2329}, {\"ngram\": \"the softly-spoken midfielder\", \"from\": 2333, \"to\": 2361}, {\"ngram\": \"his sporting inspiration\", \"from\": 2389, \"to\": 2413}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I tend to come out of myself when I am on a hockey pitch, but essentially, it's just trying to be the same as I always have been,\\\" explains Ames.\", \"from\": 2420, \"to\": 2566, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2561, \"end\": 2565, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ames_Research_Center\", \"score\": 0.9998427001934586, \"rank\": 0.00015676921140918057, \"text\": \"Ames\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ames_Research_Center\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ames_Research_Center\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a hockey pitch\", \"from\": 2463, \"to\": 2477}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think it would be foolish for me to try to change.\", \"from\": 2567, \"to\": 2620, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Roy Keane is someone I listen to a lot.\", \"from\": 2622, \"to\": 2662, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2623, \"end\": 2632, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roy_Keane\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Roy Keane\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roy_Keane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roy_Keane\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"someone\", \"from\": 2636, \"to\": 2643}, {\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 2656, \"to\": 2661}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He has a completely different mindset to me, but he speaks very openly and very truthfully about everything.\", \"from\": 2663, \"to\": 2771, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a completely different mindset\", \"from\": 2670, \"to\": 2700}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 2760, \"to\": 2770}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I have tried to do that myself-more than I perhaps should have.\\\"\", \"from\": 2772, \"to\": 2836, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ames credits the arrival of coach Paul Revington with instilling a new belief in the team - though do not call it 'Revsball', his players think his animated touchline manner is more J\\u00fcrgen Klopp.\", \"from\": 2838, \"to\": 3033, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3020, \"end\": 3032, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J\\u00fcrgen_Klopp\", \"score\": 0.9999999892861525, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"J\\u00fcrgen Klopp\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J\\u00fcrgen_Klopp\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J\\u00fcrgen_Klopp\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ames\", \"from\": 2838, \"to\": 2842}, {\"ngram\": \"the arrival\", \"from\": 2851, \"to\": 2862}, {\"ngram\": \"coach Paul Revington\", \"from\": 2866, \"to\": 2886}, {\"ngram\": \"a new belief\", \"from\": 2903, \"to\": 2915}, {\"ngram\": \"the team\", \"from\": 2919, \"to\": 2927}, {\"ngram\": \"his players\", \"from\": 2964, \"to\": 2975}, {\"ngram\": \"his animated touchline manner\", \"from\": 2982, \"to\": 3011}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Revington is a former world coach of the year, taking his native South Africa to the Olympics in 2004 before spells with Ireland, Great Britain, where he coached the women's team, and Malaysia.\", \"from\": 3035, \"to\": 3228, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3100, \"end\": 3112, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9343694060090297, \"rank\": 0.07001394813046952, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3156, \"end\": 3163, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9940744001498457, \"rank\": 0.00319901925345828, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3165, \"end\": 3178, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_men's_national_field_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999905076038, \"rank\": 6.410340701296749e-09, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_men's_national_field_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_men's_national_field_hockey_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3219, \"end\": 3227, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malaysia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.996288357326558, \"rank\": 0.00368268053020139, \"text\": \"Malaysia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malaysia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malaysia_national_football_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Revington\", \"from\": 3035, \"to\": 3044}, {\"ngram\": \"a former world coach\", \"from\": 3048, \"to\": 3068}, {\"ngram\": \"the year\", \"from\": 3072, \"to\": 3080}, 